# Integration Hub Product Platform Model

This repository implements an Integration Hub platform that connects vendors through governed, validated integrations.

The platform is not a simple API service.  
It is a multi-plane integration platform.

---

# Platform Planes

## 1 Control Plane (Admin Governance)

Purpose:
Manage integrations and platform configuration.

Responsibilities:

Vendor onboarding  
Operation definitions  
Contracts and schemas  
Allowlist rules  
Endpoint configuration  
Auth profile configuration  
Flow Builder governance  
Replay Console operations  

Primary APIs:

/v1/registry/**
/v1/admin/**

Primary UI:

apps/web-cip

Primary data schema:

control_plane.*

Control plane changes affect runtime behavior but do not execute integrations themselves.

---

## 2 Runtime Plane (Execution Engine)

Purpose:
Execute integrations safely and consistently.

Responsibilities:

Request validation  
Contract enforcement  
Payload transformation  
Downstream routing  
Audit logging  
Usage metering  

Primary APIs:

/v1/execute
/v1/ai/execute

Primary code location:

apps/api runtime lambdas

Primary data schema:

data_plane.*

Runtime plane must remain deterministic and stable.

---

## 3 Vendor Plane (Partner Interaction)

Purpose:
Allow vendors to interact with the Integration Hub.

Responsibilities:

Vendor configuration views  
Vendor integration testing  
Vendor usage metrics  
Vendor debugging tools  

Primary APIs:

/v1/vendor/**

Primary UI:

apps/web-partners

Vendor plane must enforce strict vendor isolation.

Vendor identity always comes from JWT claim:

bcpAuth

---

# Core Platform Subsystems

## Canonical Data Model

Defines standard request and response schemas for operations.

Stored in:

control_plane.operation_contracts

Vendor overrides allowed via:

control_plane.vendor_operation_contracts

Runtime validation must always use:

vendor override if present  
otherwise canonical contract

---

## Allowlist Access Model

Defines which vendor pairs may interact.

Stored in:

control_plane.vendor_operation_allowlist

Runtime must deny execution if no allowlist entry exists.

---

## Endpoint Registry

Defines downstream vendor endpoints.

Stored in:

control_plane.vendor_endpoints

Includes:

endpoint URL  
auth profile  
verification status  

Endpoint verification must be SSRF-safe.

---

## Auth Federation

External vendors may authenticate using different identity providers.

Supported providers include:

Okta  
Azure AD  
Google Cloud Identity  

Vendor identity must resolve to the claim:

bcpAuth

This claim maps to Integration Hub vendor codes.

---

## AI Formatter

AI may assist with formatting or transformation tasks.

AI usage is governed by feature gates.

AI must never change routing decisions or validation outcomes.

AI failures must not break runtime execution.

---

## Replay Console

Admin-only tool allowing transaction replay.

Replay must:

respect allowlist rules  
respect idempotency  
emit audit events  

Replay must not bypass governance checks.

---

## Usage and Billing

Usage events track integration activity.

Stored in:

usage.usage_events

Rollups stored in:

usage.usage_rollups_daily

Usage must only store metadata and never PHI.

---

# Security Principles

The platform must enforce:

Vendor isolation  
Contract validation  
Allowlist enforcement  
PHI protection  
Auditability  

All sensitive operations must generate audit events.

PHI access requires special approval groups.

---

# Feature Implementation Expectations

When implementing new platform capabilities, the agent must determine:

Which plane the feature belongs to:

Control Plane  
Runtime Plane  
Vendor Plane  

Which subsystems are affected:

Contracts  
Allowlist  
Runtime execution  
Audit  
Billing  
AI  

Features must be implemented consistently across all affected layers.

---

# Platform Goal

The Integration Hub acts as a secure, governed integration fabric that enables vendors to exchange data safely without direct point-to-point integrations.